The paper discusses the use of deep learning for decomposing conventional X-ray images into independent sub-volumes, which is a problem related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the challenge of modeling such a problem, which suggests the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper involves the use of medical imaging, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and neural engineering (cs.NE) categories.
